<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="285" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860N.85/1</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                                State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-31">October 31, 1940</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Soviet Ambassador called to see me.</p>
                        <p>The Ambassador again undertook a discourse upon the subject of Baltic
                            ships within United States jurisdiction.</p>
                        <p>I stated that I would investigate the matter further and would discuss
                            the problem with him once more in an early conversation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps">elles</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>